Step 1: Start

User opens the application.

Check if the user is logged in.

If NOT logged in ‚Üí Redirect to login page.

If logged in ‚Üí Show dashboard.

Step 2: Upload CSV File

User goes to Upload Analysis page.

User selects a CSV file.

System reads the file.

Remove empty rows from the file.

Store the cleaned data.

Step 3: Send Data for AI Analysis

Show loading message: "Analyzing data..."

Send machine data to backend (Supabase function).

Backend checks:

If API key exists.

If request is valid.

Step 4: AI Processing

Backend sends machine data to AI model.

AI analyzes:

Load

Speed

Temperature

Vibration

Runtime hours

Maintenance patterns

For each machine, AI calculates:

Servicing probability (0‚Äì100%)

Risk level (Low / Medium / High / Critical)

Key indicators

Recommended action

Priority score (1‚Äì10)

AI also generates:

Total machines

Number of critical machines

Average risk

Overall recommendations

Backend sends results back to frontend.

Step 5: Display Results

Stop loading.

Show summary:

Total machines

Critical machines

Average risk

Recommendations

For each machine:

Show Machine ID

Show Risk level

Show Servicing probability

Show Key indicators

Show Recommended action

Show Priority score

Step 6: Download Report

If user clicks Download CSV:

Convert results into CSV format.

Download file.

If user clicks Download PDF:

Create PDF report.

Add summary.

Add machine table.

Download file.

Step 7: End

User can upload another file or logout.

System ends.

